<h2>Project Overview</h2>

This project involved designing an **instrumented 3/8-inch drive torque wrench** rated for  
**600 in·lbf**, integrating analytical calculations, CAD modeling, strain-gauge placement,  
and ANSYS finite-element validation.

The wrench needed to meet:

- Sensitivity requirement of **≥ 1.0 mV/V**  
- Yield/brittle failure factor of safety: **X₀ ≥ 4**  
- Crack-growth safety factor: **Xₖ ≥ 2**  
- Fatigue safety factor: **Xₛ ≥ 1.5**  
- Compatibility with standard bonded foil gauges  
- Manufacturability and repeatable strain fields  

---

<h2>Baseline Analysis</h2>

Using assigned dimensions, the baseline design produced:

- **Deflection (load point):** 0.091 in  
- **Max bending stress:** 12.8 ksi  
- **Strain at gauge:** 375 µε  
- **Estimated output:** 0.38 mV/V (half-bridge)

<table>
<thead>
<tr><th>Failure Mode</th><th>Safety Factor</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Static Strength</td><td>28.9</td></tr>
<tr><td>Crack Growth</td><td>2.95</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fatigue</td><td>8.98</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

The baseline design was structurally sound but **did not meet the sensitivity requirement**, motivating a redesign.

---

<h2>Improved Final Design</h2>

Design adjustments focused on:

- Increasing measurable strain at the gauge  
- Introducing a controlled reduced section  
- Maintaining yield, fatigue, and fracture safety margins  
- Creating flat gauge-mount surfaces  

<div align="center">
<img src="{{ '/assets/images/torque-wrench-cover.png' | relative_url }}" alt="CAD geometry" style="max-width:90%; border-radius:8px;">
<p><em>Final CAD geometry modeled in Fusion 360.</em></p>
</div>

---

<h2>Material Selection</h2>

The selected alloy:

**Aluminum 7475-T7651**

- Young’s Modulus: 10 × 10⁶ psi  
- Poisson Ratio: 0.29  
- Ultimate Strength: ~65 ksi  
- Fracture Toughness: ~46 ksi√in  

This material offers favorable fatigue resistance and ductility while supporting a narrower reduced section for strain amplification.

---

<h2>Finite Element Analysis (ANSYS)</h2>

**Boundary Conditions**

- Drive end constrained over top 0.40 in  
- Applied torsional moment equivalent to **600 in·lbf**  

### FEM Outputs

<table>
<thead>
<tr><th>Quantity</th><th>Value</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Maximum Normal Stress</td><td>133.75 ksi</td></tr>
<tr><td>Load-Point Deflection</td><td>0.38077 in</td></tr>
<tr><td>Gauge-Location Strains (x, y, z)</td><td>−0.3059, −0.30605, 1.055 millistrain</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

