---

<h2>Sensitivity Prediction (mV/V)</h2>

A half-bridge Wheatstone output was estimated using:

<div style="background:#f6f8fa; padding:12px; border-radius:6px;">
Approximate output:  
<br>Vout/Vin ≈ (Gauge Factor × 2 × Strain) / 4  
<br>Using GF ≈ 2.05 and ε ≈ 1.055 × 10⁻³  
</div>

**Final Sensitivity:**  
➡ **≥ 1.0 mV/V at 600 in·lbf** (requirement satisfied)

---

<h2>Strain Gauge Selection</h2>

**Selected Gauge:** Vishay EA-06-125BZ-350  
**Type:** Linear foil gauge, 350 Ω, GF ≈ 2.05  

<table>
<thead><tr><th>Gauge Parameter</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Grid Length</td><td>3.18 mm</td></tr>
<tr><td>Grid Width</td><td>1.57 mm</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pattern Type</td><td>Linear</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

This gauge fits the redesigned mounting surface and matches the FEM-predicted strain levels.

---

<h2>Conclusion</h2>

The final torque-wrench configuration:

- Meets all structural and fatigue criteria  
- Achieves **over twice the sensitivity** of the baseline design  
- Provides clean strain fields for half-bridge measurement  
- Integrates CAD, materials, strain-gauges, and FEM into a cohesive design process  

---
